## Awareness Stage
- **User Story 1**: 
  - **Action**: Emily discovers TrailStride a hiking shoe company through an Instagram post by a popular hiker influencer reviewing the shoe.
  - **Acceptance**: Emily follows TrailStride on Instagram for updates.
- **User Story 2**
  - **Action**: Emily searches for "best sustainable hiking shoes" on Google and finds a blog post from TrailStride's website ranking at the top of search results.
  - **Acceptance**: Emily reads the blog post, browses through the TrailStride website for more information on their sustainability practices, and signs up for the TrailStride newsletter to learn more about their products and initiatives.
  ## Interest Stage
- **User Story 1**: 
  - **Action**: Emily stumbles upon an engaging article shared on social media about the impact of quality hiking shoes on trail safety, published by TrailStride. The article includes an infographic highlighting how TrailStride's 5% sales donation contributes to trail conservation.
  - **Acceptance**: Emily shares the article with their social network, spreading the word about TrailStrideâ€™s commitment to safety and conservation.
- **User Story 2**
  - **Action**:  Emily, a hiking enthusiast, attends a TrailStride-hosted webinar on hiking tips and trail conservation. During the webinar, a customer shares a testimonial about their positive experience with TrailStride shoes on a recent hike.
  - **Acceptance**: Emily registers for the webinar and attends it without technical difficulties. Emily feels more connected to the TrailStride brand and browses the hiking shoe selection on the TrailStride website within a week of attending the webinar.
    ## Decision Stage
- **User Story 1**: 
  - **Action**: Emily is comparing different brands of hiking shoes online and comes across a product comparison chart on TrailStride's website that highlights the unique benefits of their shoes, including their eco-friendly materials and durability.
  - **Acceptance**: Emily is able to easily locate and understand the comparison chart on the TrailStride website.The chart clearly differentiates TrailStride shoes based on comfort, durability, and use of eco-friendly materials compared to two other leading brands.Emily feels informed enough to make a purchase decision and adds a pair of TrailStride shoes to their online cart.
- **User Story 2**
  - **Action**: Emily, who has purchased from TrailStride before, receives an email about a loyalty program that offers discounts on future purchases. The email also includes an exclusive preview of an upcoming shoe design with new features.
  - **Acceptance**: Emily opens the email and the content clearly explains the benefits of the loyalty program. Emily is able to successfully sign up for the loyalty program through a link provided in the email. Emily expresses interest in the new shoe design by clicking on the 'Notify Me on Launch' button.
  ## Action Stage
- **User Story 1**: 
  - **Action**: Emily is looking to buy hiking shoes online and chooses TrailStride because of its easy-to-use website. Emily uses the guide provided to select the right shoes for rocky terrain.
  - **Acceptance**: Emily finds the navigation of the TrailStride website intuitive and can locate the guide on choosing shoes within two clicks from the homepage. After reading the guide, Emily can confidently select the appropriate shoe size and type for rocky terrains. Emily completes the purchase without any issues and feels satisfied with the information provided that influenced their choice.
- **User Story 2**
  - **Action**: Emily has selected a pair of hiking shoes from TrailStride and proceeds to check out, appreciating the multiple payment options and the clear, concise product description that confirmed their decision.
  - **Acceptance**: At checkout, Emily finds all relevant product information summarized and confirms it matches their expectations.Emily is presented with at least three different payment options, including credit card, PayPal, and an alternative payment method.Emily completes the transaction smoothly, receives a confirmation email within minutes, and accesses customer support for an estimated delivery time.
    